      <billSummaries>
        <item>
          <lastSummaryUpdateDate>2018-02-12T18:09:32Z</lastSummaryUpdateDate>
          <text><![CDATA[<p><b>Strengthening Children's Safety Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to add violent state crimes to the list of violent offenses that trigger an additional five-year consecutive mandatory minimum prison term for a defendant who fails to comply with sex offender registration requirements and commits such offense.</p> <p>Additionally, it expands the prior military sex offense convictions that trigger an enhanced mandatory minimum prison term for a defendant who subsequently commits aggravated child sex abuse or certain child pornography offenses.</p>]]></text>
          <actionDesc>Introduced in House</actionDesc>
          <actionDate>2017-03-30</actionDate>
          <name>Introduced in House</name>
          <updateDate>2017-03-30T04:00:00Z</updateDate>
